05:09.208 --> 05:11.583
DETECTIVE ( on TV ):

05:09.208 --> 05:11.583
I was an island of law,

05:11.625 --> 05:13.834
afloat in an ocean

05:11.625 --> 05:13.834
of crime waves.

05:13.875 --> 05:16.083
I'd been undercover

05:13.875 --> 05:16.083
for so long,

05:16.125 --> 05:18.250
my own chief

05:16.125 --> 05:18.250
didn't recognize me.

05:18.291 --> 05:21.041
It was worth it,

05:18.291 --> 05:21.041
if it meant blowing the lid off

05:21.083 --> 05:24.000
the biggest crime spree

05:21.083 --> 05:24.000
in Cincinnati.

05:24.041 --> 05:26.083
Undercover.

05:26.125 --> 05:29.208
I believe now I understand.

05:31.000 --> 05:32.583
CODY:

05:31.000 --> 05:32.583
Do you guys know where Chase is?

05:32.625 --> 05:34.000
Haven't seen him

05:32.625 --> 05:34.000
all morning.

05:34.041 --> 05:35.750
I thought if he practiced

05:34.041 --> 05:35.750
my script with me,

05:35.792 --> 05:37.834
he'd see why

05:35.792 --> 05:37.834
pretending's so fun.

05:37.875 --> 05:41.208
First you might have to

05:37.875 --> 05:41.208
explain to him what "fun" means.

05:41.250 --> 05:43.709
The air was heavy,

05:43.750 --> 05:46.166
heavy with the fog

05:43.750 --> 05:46.166
of lawlessness.

05:46.208 --> 05:47.875
That's when she walked in...

05:46.208 --> 05:47.875
( door slides open )

05:50.041 --> 05:54.500
...and asked me the one question

05:50.041 --> 05:54.500
I wasn't prepared to answer.

05:54.542 --> 05:56.250
Why is it so dark in here?

05:56.291 --> 05:59.041
Chase? Is there a reason you're

05:56.291 --> 05:59.041
in here with the lights off?

05:59.083 --> 06:01.000
I am using

05:59.083 --> 06:01.000
my imagination to expand

06:01.041 --> 06:02.667
my law enforcement tactics.

06:02.709 --> 06:04.875
Yeah, okay.

06:04.917 --> 06:06.917
And where'd

06:04.917 --> 06:06.917
you get the hat?

06:06.959 --> 06:09.542
My life is full

06:06.959 --> 06:09.542
of mysteries.

06:11.291 --> 06:14.083
The internet. Apparently

06:11.291 --> 06:14.083
one size really does fit all.

06:14.125 --> 06:15.750
CODY:

06:14.125 --> 06:15.750
Whoa. I think someone's

06:15.792 --> 06:18.166
trying to hijack

06:15.792 --> 06:18.166
Huxley's broadcast.

06:18.208 --> 06:22.542
HUXLEY ( on TV ):

06:18.208 --> 06:22.542
And what safety techniques

06:18.208 --> 06:22.542
should we be aware of, Mayor?

06:22.583 --> 06:25.917
MAYOR ( on TV ):

06:22.583 --> 06:25.917
Well, if you ever see

06:22.583 --> 06:25.917
an unattended crawfish

06:25.959 --> 06:28.709
you should immediate--

06:25.959 --> 06:28.709
HUXLEY: Wait, cut.

06:28.750 --> 06:30.750
Something's wrong

06:28.750 --> 06:30.750
with my news feed.

06:30.792 --> 06:32.750
Hey! Who are they?

06:32.792 --> 06:35.250
( both grunting )

06:35.291 --> 06:36.792
No, stop.  What are you--?

06:38.542 --> 06:42.500
Guess Evan and Myles

06:38.542 --> 06:42.500
don't like Crawfish Week either.

06:42.542 --> 06:45.208
Cody, keep an eye on those two

06:42.542 --> 06:45.208
from the Command Center.

06:45.250 --> 06:46.625
Team.

06:46.667 --> 06:49.625
Rescue Bots,

06:46.667 --> 06:49.625
