06:49.667 --> 06:52.041
(  upbeat theme playing  )

07:01.917 --> 07:04.291
( police siren wailing )

07:08.125 --> 07:11.792
CHASE:

07:08.125 --> 07:11.792
The sound of my squealing tires

07:08.125 --> 07:11.792
echoed across the landscape...

07:11.834 --> 07:14.250
Chase, are you narrating?

07:14.291 --> 07:17.500
I'm using my imagination

07:14.291 --> 07:17.500
to stay in character.

07:17.542 --> 07:19.834
Filmic evidence shows

07:17.542 --> 07:19.834
this behavior is 99.8 percent

07:19.875 --> 07:21.667
effective when solving crimes.

07:21.709 --> 07:24.875
Well, if it means catching

07:21.709 --> 07:24.875
Evan and Myles, I'm all for it.

07:24.917 --> 07:26.709
CODY ( on com ):

07:24.917 --> 07:26.709
Dad. Evan and Myles are about

07:26.750 --> 07:28.959
to drive off

07:26.750 --> 07:28.959
with Huxley's satellite dish.

07:29.000 --> 07:30.500
What do they need that for?

07:30.542 --> 07:31.834
Maybe they want to watch

07:31.875 --> 07:33.750
the  Pets on Ice  marathon.

07:33.792 --> 07:35.667
I doubt it's that innocent,

07:33.792 --> 07:35.667
Blades.

07:35.709 --> 07:37.583
I'd give anything

07:35.709 --> 07:37.583
to know exactly

07:37.625 --> 07:38.959
what those two are planning.

07:39.000 --> 07:40.542
Hmm.

07:40.583 --> 07:42.667
( GPS beeping )

07:40.583 --> 07:42.667
Dad, they're on Russell Street.

07:42.709 --> 07:44.208
You can cut them off on First.

07:44.250 --> 07:46.834
You heard Cody, team.

07:44.250 --> 07:46.834
Form a roadblock.

07:46.875 --> 07:48.792
Chase and I

07:46.875 --> 07:48.792
will sneak up from behind.

07:48.834 --> 07:51.208
(  dramatic theme playing  )

07:56.542 --> 07:58.000
And in case we're not

07:56.542 --> 07:58.000
enough of a threat,

07:58.041 --> 08:00.250
this trip wire will be.

08:07.125 --> 08:08.792
( tires screech )

08:20.583 --> 08:21.792
Whoa.

08:25.083 --> 08:26.500
Whoa.

08:26.542 --> 08:27.709
( tires popping )

08:35.750 --> 08:38.542
Shouldn't have left

08:35.750 --> 08:38.542
your car running, Chief.

08:38.583 --> 08:41.500
They actually think they

08:38.583 --> 08:41.500
can use Chase as a getaway car?

08:41.542 --> 08:43.250
Heh. Can't wait

08:41.542 --> 08:43.250
to see this.

08:43.291 --> 08:46.166
( engine revs, tires screech )

08:46.208 --> 08:49.625
Any second now,

08:46.208 --> 08:49.625
Chase'll slam on the brakes.

08:49.667 --> 08:51.750
Any second...

08:51.792 --> 08:53.208
Or not.

08:53.250 --> 08:54.667
Where's he going?

08:54.709 --> 08:56.166
Chief, do something.

08:56.208 --> 08:58.542
Chase is the victim

08:56.208 --> 08:58.542
of grand theft Autobot.

08:58.583 --> 09:01.834
But Blades, nobody can make you

08:58.583 --> 09:01.834
Bots do what you don't want do.

09:01.875 --> 09:03.792
Trust me, I've tried.

09:03.834 --> 09:06.000
You think Chase wanted

09:03.834 --> 09:06.000
to go with Evan and Myles

09:06.041 --> 09:07.709
